From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VerteDinde <vertedinde@electronjs.org>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 15:17:53 -0700
Subject: fix: handle render process reuse in RendererStartupHelper on all
 platforms

RendererStartupHelper::OnRenderProcessLaunched() CHECKs that any
non-guest process belonging to its BrowserContext was registered when
OnRenderProcessHostCreated() was dispatched. That invariant breaks when
a RenderProcessHost is re-initialized from inside the process-death
notification: an observer that runs before RendererStartupHelper (for
example an app calling webContents.reload() synchronously from the
'render-process-gone' event, which is emitted inside
RenderProcessHostImpl::ProcessDied()'s observer loop) re-enters
RenderProcessHostImpl::Init(). The OnRenderProcessHostCreated()
dispatch from that re-init is ignored because the stale
process_mojo_map_ entry from the previous renderer is still present,
RendererStartupHelper then untracks the process when its own
RenderProcessExited() runs, and once the relaunched process finishes
launching, OnRenderProcessLaunched() finds no registration and the
CHECK brings down the browser process.

Chromium hit the same race and replaced the CHECK with a graceful
re-register on Android (crrev.com/c/7330559) and ChromeOS
(crrev.com/c/7862000, crbug.com/512916518). The race is
platform-agnostic, so apply the same handling on all platforms.

This patch can be removed when upstream drops the platform guard
around the re-register path.

diff --git a/extensions/browser/renderer_startup_helper.cc b/extensions/browser/renderer_startup_helper.cc
index cacaf4fe5faf634e263546bef9111b8841ec1297..0bede7652a2975c4227eb3790a4f31521d849c7c 100644
--- a/extensions/browser/renderer_startup_helper.cc
+++ b/extensions/browser/renderer_startup_helper.cc
@@ -266,13 +266,22 @@ void RendererStartupHelper::OnRenderProcessLaunched(
     // extensions should have already been initialized in
     // OnRenderProcessHostCreated(), if it corresponds to the same context.
     ExtensionsBrowserClient* client = ExtensionsBrowserClient::Get();
-#if BUILDFLAG(IS_ANDROID) || BUILDFLAG(IS_CHROMEOS)
-    // On Android and ChromeOS, handle race condition during process restart:
+    // Handle a race condition during process restart (upstream applies this
+    // only on Android and ChromeOS, but it is reachable on all platforms in
+    // Electron — for example when an app calls webContents.reload()
+    // synchronously from the 'render-process-gone' event, which is emitted
+    // inside the RenderProcessHost's process-death observer loop):
     // 1. OnRenderProcessHostCreated() initializes extensions and populates
     // process_mojo_map_.
-    // 2. Process startup fails in some cases.
-    // 3. RenderProcessExited() clears process_mojo_map_ via UntrackProcess().
-    // 4. The process is reused and OnRenderProcessLaunched() is still called.
+    // 2. The renderer process exits or fails to launch.
+    // 3. An observer notified before this one re-enters
+    // RenderProcessHostImpl::Init(), whose OnRenderProcessHostCreated()
+    // dispatch is ignored here because the stale process_mojo_map_ entry
+    // from the previous renderer is still present.
+    // 4. RenderProcessExited() then clears process_mojo_map_ via
+    // UntrackProcess().
+    // 5. The relaunched process reaches OnRenderProcessLaunched() with no
+    // registration, which used to fail a CHECK on desktop platforms.
     //
     // Re-register the process to restore Mojo communication without
     // re-initializing extensions to avoid duplicate loading.
@@ -280,10 +289,6 @@ void RendererStartupHelper::OnRenderProcessLaunched(
         client->IsSameContext(browser_context_, host->GetBrowserContext())) {
       RegisterProcess(host);
     }
-#else
-    CHECK(GetRenderer(host) != nullptr ||
-          !client->IsSameContext(browser_context_, host->GetBrowserContext()));
-#endif  // BUILDFLAG(IS_ANDROID) || BUILDFLAG(IS_CHROMEOS)
     return;
   }
   // Otherwise, we should *not* have initialized the host yet.
